The Command-Line To-Do List application is a simple yet powerful tool designed to help users manage and organize their tasks efficiently. 
Built using Python, this application allows users to perform basic operations on their to-do lists, such as adding, updating, deleting, and viewing tasks, all from the command line. 
This project is ideal for beginners who want to learn the fundamentals of Python programming and command-line interface (CLI) development.

Features
    Add Tasks: Users can add new tasks to their to-do list.
    Update Tasks: Users can update existing tasks with new descriptions.
    Delete Tasks: Users can remove tasks from their to-do list.
    View Tasks: Users can view all the tasks currently in their to-do list.
    Clear Screen: The application includes a function to clear the terminal screen for better readability.
    User-Friendly Menu: A simple and intuitive menu-driven interface guides users through the available options.

Technology Stack
    Programming Language: Python
    Libraries: Standard Python library (no additional packages required)
    Environment: Command-line interface (CLI)

Code Structure
    ToDoList Class:
        Manages the list of tasks and provides methods to add, update, delete, and view tasks.
        Stores tasks in a list, with each task being a simple string.

    Functions:
        clear_screen(): Clears the terminal screen based on the operating system.
        main(): The main function that provides a menu-driven interface for user interaction. It continuously prompts the user for actions and calls the appropriate methods on the ToDoList instance.

How to Use
    Run the Application:
        Save the script to a file (e.g., todo.py).
        Open the terminal or command prompt.
        Navigate to the directory where the script is saved.
        Run the script using the command python todo.py.

    Interact with the Application:
        Choose from the menu options to add, update, delete, or view tasks.
        Follow the prompts to enter task descriptions or IDs as needed.
        Exit the application by selecting the "Exit" option from the menu.
